We start by noting that the paid‐in capital is normally established at the company’s setup and then usually remains unchanged in the course of regular operations (unless additional capital is contributed later). In our provided transactions the only “Initial” records are as follows:

• Initial20231231001 – Cash deposit: 3,000,000.0  
• Initial20231231001 – Bank deposit: 5,000,000.0  
• Initial20231231001 – Fixed Assets: 5,000,000.0  

Adding these gives:

  3,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 + 5,000,000.0 = 13,000,000.0

No other transactions indicate further contributions or changes to the paid‐in capital. Therefore the initial (and final) paid‐in capital remains 13,000,000.00.
